\title{Figma}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Use the Figma MCP server to fetch design context, screenshots, variables, and assets from Figma, and to translate Figma nodes into production code. Trigger when a task involves Figma URLs, node IDs, design-to-code implementation, or Figma MCP setup and troubleshooting.}

\subtree{
\title{Figma MCP}
\p{Use the Figma MCP server for Figma-driven implementation. For setup and debugging details (env vars, config, verification), see \code{\startverb references/figma-mcp-config.md\stopverb}.}

\subtree{
\title{Figma MCP Integration Rules}
\p{These rules define how to translate Figma inputs into code for this project and must be followed for every Figma-driven change.}

\subtree{
\title{Required flow (do not skip)}
\ol{
\li{Run get_design_context first to fetch the structured representation for the exact node(s).}
\li{If the response is too large or truncated, run get_metadata to get the high-level node map and then re-fetch only the required node(s) with get_design_context.}
\li{Run get_screenshot for a visual reference of the node variant being implemented.}
\li{Only after you have both get_design_context and get_screenshot, download any assets needed and start implementation.}
\li{Translate the output (usually React + Tailwind) into this project's conventions, styles and framework. Reuse the project's color tokens, components, and typography wherever possible.}
\li{Validate against Figma for 1:1 look and behavior before marking complete.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Implementation rules}
\ul{
\li{Treat the Figma MCP output (React + Tailwind) as a representation of design and behavior, not as final code style.}
\li{Replace Tailwind utility classes with the project's preferred utilities/design-system tokens when applicable.}
\li{Reuse existing components (e.g., buttons, inputs, typography, icon wrappers) instead of duplicating functionality.}
\li{Use the project's color system, typography scale, and spacing tokens consistently.}
\li{Respect existing routing, state management, and data-fetch patterns already adopted in the repo.}
\li{Strive for 1:1 visual parity with the Figma design. When conflicts arise, prefer design-system tokens and adjust spacing or sizes minimally to match visuals.}
\li{Validate the final UI against the Figma screenshot for both look and behavior.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Asset handling}
\ul{
\li{The Figma MCP Server provides an assets endpoint which can serve image and SVG assets.}
\li{IMPORTANT: If the Figma MCP Server returns a localhost source for an image or an SVG, use that image or SVG source directly.}
\li{IMPORTANT: DO NOT import/add new icon packages, all the assets should be in the Figma payload.}
\li{IMPORTANT: do NOT use or create placeholders if a localhost source is provided.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Link-based prompting}
\ul{
\li{The server is link-based: copy the Figma frame/layer link and give that URL to the MCP client when asking for implementation help.}
\li{The client cannot browse the URL but extracts the node ID from the link; always ensure the link points to the exact node/variant you want.}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{References}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb references/figma-mcp-config.md\stopverb} — setup, verification, troubleshooting, and link-based usage reminders.}
\li{\code{\startverb references/figma-tools-and-prompts.md\stopverb} — tool catalog and prompt patterns for selecting frameworks/components and fetching metadata.}
}
}
}